{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Kendall's "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"\\tau"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" and Somers' "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"D"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" are rank order statistics. They measure the degree of comonotonic dependence of two random variables. Comonotonic dependence generalises linear dependence that is expressed via linear correlation."}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Let "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"X"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" and "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"Y"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" be random variables. Kendall's "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"\\tau"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" is then defined as "}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"    "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":true,"texString":"\\tau_{XY} = P(X_1 < X_2, Y_1 < Y_2) + P(X_1 > X_2, Y_1 > Y_2) - P(X_1 < X_2, Y_1 > Y_2) - P(X_1 > X_2, Y_1 < Y_2),"}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"where "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"(X_1, Y_1)"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" and "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"(X_2, Y_2)"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" are independent copies of "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"(X,Y)"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":". So "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"\\tau_{XY}"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" is the difference between the probabilities of the "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"X"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"'s being in the same order as the "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"Y"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"'s and that of the "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"X"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"'s being in the opposite order as the "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"Y"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"'s. "}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Somers' "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"D"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" is defined as"}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"    "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"D_{XY} = \\frac{\\tau_{XY}}{\\tau_{YY}}\n"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":","}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"i.e. Kendall "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"\\tau"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":" given that the "},
{"className":"EquationNode","text":"","encoding":"tex","mathmlString":"","displayStyle":false,"texString":"Y"},
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"-values aren't equal."}]},
{"className":"RichTextParagraphNode","align":"left","children":[
{"className":"RichTextNode","text":"Somers' D maybe interpreted as a generalisation of the accuracy ratio. The closer Somers' D score is to 1, the better the rating model. "}]},
